#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/true_winds.rst:22
msgid "True Winds (Foreign Grid)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/true_winds.rst:24
msgid ""
"This example demonstrates how to render \"true\" winds, when attached to "
"data points given in a non-standard Coordinate Reference System (CRS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/true_winds.rst:28
msgid "📋 Summary"
msgstr "📋 まとめ"

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/true_winds.rst:30
msgid ""
"The example constructs sample points on a North Polar Stereographic grid, "
"and assigns synthetic vector values to them, representing wind data. These "
"data are presented as \"true\" winds, i.e., eastward (``U``) and northward "
"(``V``) vector components, therefore not related to the foreign sample "
"points grid. This is a fairly typical real world use case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/true_winds.rst:36
msgid ""
"A synthetic eastward wind with a constant ``4.0 ms-1`` is generated "
"everywhere, so the final effect is clearly visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/true_winds.rst:39
msgid ""
"We use the :meth:`geovista.bridge.Transform.from_points` method, passing the"
" winds to the ``vectors`` keyword, and specifying the different CRS of both "
"the sample points (``crs``) and the vectors (``vectors_crs``)."
msgstr ""

